    "body": "I run this script from` [Joaquim's image]( http://fct-gmt.ualg.pt/tmp/cor_verdadeira.tiff) and I get a figure very tall (11 m). This only appears when a color is used for the facade (-N+gcolor) and drapeimage (-G).\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\ngmt grdview @earth_relief_15s -R-9.5/-8.7/38.4/39.1/-2000/400 -JM14c -JZ4c -p160/35 -Qi -Vi  \\\r\n\t-Wf0.5 -BnSwEZ -Baf -Bzaf+l\"Altura (m)\" -N-2000+ggreen -Gcor_verdadeira.tiff  -pdf Lisboa\r\n```\r\n```\r\npsconvert [INFORMATION]: Figure dimensions: Width: 594.468 points [20.9715 cm]  Height: 32767 points [1155.95 cm]\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n[Lisboa.pdf](https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/gmt/files/7079344/Lisboa.pdf)\r\n\r\n\r\nScreen Capture of the ps:\r\n![imagen](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17908951/131398907-123e958f-f93b-4efe-974e-ff58f0ebfabd.png)\r\n\r\n",
